oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Big Mac Attack for Information Management
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Boomer, W. Gene
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Time management
veterinary practice
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Time management consultants encourage us to plan our day--either before retiring at night or early in the morning. I am an early riser so I try to spend 15-20 minutes early each morning planning my day--listing, prioritizing, and visualizing the day ahead. This technique has been very successful for me. I know many others in the organization that do the same.
